adjective.description: That goes through something; (later especially) passing through, travelling through.
Originally Scottish. That provides a way or route through; especially designating a street or passageway which is open at both ends, as opposed to a cul-de-sac or dead end.
Chiefly Scottish, Irish English (northern), and United States regional. Of a person: that gets through work quickly or thoroughly; active, energetic; persevering.

Of a person or personal attribute: exemplifying a specified characteristic fully; absolute, extreme, out-and-out. Of an action, process, etc.: involving or dealing with every detail or aspect of something.
